text: Keith Jobling (26 March 1934 â€“ 20 September 2020) was an English professional footballer. He was born in New Waltham, Lincolnshire. He made 450 appearances in the Football League as a centre half for Grimsby Town. After leaving Grimsby he joined Boston United, first as a player and then as a manager.
